quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  23,105,Were not My signs read to you? But you used to deny them
  23,106,"They will say, \"Our Fosterer! our misfortune prevailed over us and we became a misguided people"
  23,107,"Our Fosterer ! take us out of this, if we again return (to evil) then we will certainly be unjust"
  23,108,"He will say, \"Go away into it and do not speak to Me"
  23,109,"There was a party from among My servants who said: Our Fosterer ! we believe, so protectively forgive us and have mercy on us and you are the Best of those who are merciful"
  23,110,But you took them as a ridicule to the extent that they made you forget (even) My remembrance and you used to laugh at (some) of them
  23,111,"I have rewarded them this day because they were patient, they are certainly the achievers (of success)"
  23,112,"He will say, \"How long did you stay in the earth, counting in years"
  23,113,"They will say, \"We stayed for a day or part of a day but ask those who keep the account"
  23,114,"He will say, \"You did not stay but a little, had you but known"
  23,115,Did you then think that We created you without any purpose and that you will not be returned to Us
  23,116,"So Highly Exalted is Allah the Real King, there is no god except Him, Lord of the honoured throne (of the universe)"
  23,117,"And he who prays to another (presumed) god along with Allah, having no proof with him of it (being a god), then (the responsibility of taking) his account (rests) only on Allah. The infidels will certainly not be successful"
  23,118,"And say, \"My Fosterer! protectively forgive and have mercy and You are the Best of those who are merciful"